Ethiopia is constructing one of Africa's biggest dams, which will generate huge amounts of electricity to power its industrial revolution and to sell to surrounding countries. But by controlling the flow of the Blue Nile, which supplies more than 85% of the river's water, it has angered Egypt, which has traditionally had final say over which countries get how much water. Tension between the two countries can also threaten its existing relationship. --SABC--

